build/bin
node_modules

# main.go has `//go:embed all:frontend/web-build` — a fresh clone must
# still compile with `go build ./...` even without a frontend build having
# run. `.gitkeep` (a dotfile) is embedded by the `all:` prefix, so the
# embed target always exists; the actual built assets remain ignored.
#
# Vite's output dir is deliberately named `web-build`, not the default
# `dist` — the repo root .gitignore blanket-ignores any directory named
# `dist/` anywhere in the tree, and a nested .gitignore cannot re-include
# a path once a parent pattern excludes the whole directory. See
# vite.config.ts.
frontend/web-build/*
!frontend/web-build/.gitkeep
frontend/package.json.md5

# Generated by `wails generate module` / `wails dev` / `wails build` from
# the App struct's exported methods. Regenerate with `wails generate module`
# after changing any Wails-bound method signature — never hand-edit.
frontend/wailsjs
